
[1]vesture

   VEST'URE, n. [See Vest.]

   1. A garment; a robe.

   There polish'd chests embroider'd vesture grac'd.

   2. Dress; garments in general; habit; clothing; vestment; as the
   vesture of priests.

   3. Clothing; covering.

   Rocks, precipices and gulfs appareled with a vesture of plants.

   - And gild the humble vestures of the plain.

   4. In old law books, the corn with which land was covered; as the
   vesture of an acre.

   5. In old books, seisin; possession. Obs.
